  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f1003d80bc1d949f33a91ac700e48d",
        "content": [
          "* Cohort definition: Assign each user (CID) to exactly one period based on their registration date.\r\n",
          "* Acquisition funnel steps: \r\n",
          "  1. Registration\r\n",
          "  2. Verification Level 1 (input name and address)\r\n",
          "  3. Verification Level 2 (complete KYC questionnaire)\r\n",
          "  4. Verification Level 3 (pass additional checks, including user screening, electronic verification, POI, POA, phone verification, email verification, and other services)\r\n",
          "  5. First Time Deposit (FTD)\r\n",
          "  6. First Action (First Action)\r\n",
          "* Time-based grouping and filtering: Use the registration date (Step 1 date) unless a specific step is explicitly requested.\r\n",
          "* FTD calculations: Use the FirstDepositDate (or First_Time_Deposit_DateTime) when asked about FTDs.\r\n",
          "* Registration date queries: Use the registered (or Registration_DateTime) when asked about registered or registration date.\r\n",
          "* Country standardization: \r\n",
          "  - Map \"USA\", \"US\", \"UNITED STATES\" to \"United States\"\r\n",
          "  - Map \"UK\" to \"United Kingdom\"\r\n",
          "  - Map \"IL\" to \"Israel\"\r\n",
          "  - Map \"FR\", \"FRANCE\" to \"France\"\r\n",
          "  - Map \"DE\", \"GERMANY\" to \"Germany\"\r\n",
          "  - Map \"JP\", \"JAPAN\" to \"Japan\"\r\n",
          "  - Always use the full country name when filtering or grouping by country."
        ]
      }
